<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-24 02:02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Patron of bar killed  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) - A 26-year-old man is dead after being
stabbed in a bar filled with customers, according to police.
</P>
<P>
   Thomas Nimmons was pronounced dead at Albany Medical Center
Hospital shortly after the stabbing near Jernie's Cafe, city police
Detective James Miller said.
</P>
<P>
   Nimmons' death was Albany's fifth homicide this year.
</P>
<P>
   Nimmons was seen by Jernie's patrons leaving with two men
following an argument inside the bar, Miller said.
</P>
<P>
   Nimmons returned to Jernie's after being stabbed in the chest,
police said. A bouncer brought Nimmons inside, where he collapsed,
Miller said.
</P>
<P>
   Bar workers evacuated the hundreds of bar patrons following the
stabbing, possibly trampling over evidence, Miller said.
</P>
<P>
   Darnell Lashley has been arrested for the stabbing and faces
second- degree murder and criminal possession of a weapon charges
in the death of Nimmons.
</P>
<P>
   He is being held without bail at Albany County Jail.
</P>
</TEXT>
