<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-24 02:22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> An inmate walks off prison campus, still missing  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   OTISVILLE, N.Y. (AP) - A 35-year-old inmate remains at large
after walking away from prison work detail at the Otisville Federal
Correctional Facility.
</P>
<P>
   Enrique Gray-Santana was serving time for drug possession. No
description of the escaped man was available.
</P>
<P>
   State Police were on the lookout for the fugitive, as were U.S.
marshals. Gray-Santana was noticed missing at about 3:45 p.m.
Saturday, said prison spokesman Paul Ott.
</P>
<P>
   He apparently was working on the prison campus when he fled. Ott
said Gray-Santana is not dangerous, and residents should not be
concerned about their safety.
</P>
<P>
   Gray-Santana seems to have simply walked away from the
minimum-security prison. He was a resident of the prison's
satellite camp, an annex next to the prison.
</P>
<P>
   The circumstances of Gray-Santana's escape remained under
investigation last night. To live in the satellite camp, inmates
must have no history of violence or escape.
</P>
<P>
   Gray-Santana has no prior escapes or attempts, prison officials
said. He had been in Otisville for about two years. He has seven
years remaining on his sentence.
</P>
<P>
   Otisville Federal Correctional Facility is a minimum-security
facility with about 1,200 inmates. About 108 inmates are confined
to the satellite camp.
</P>
<P>
   Otisville is about 60 miles north of New York City.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
