<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Falls 21; Nasdaq Gains 14  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is down 21
points in today's early going. Advancing and declining issues are
evenly split on the New York Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is ahead 14 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is down fractionally.
</P>
<P>
   Merger news could help the market overcome any remnants from
Friday's weakness.
</P>
<P>
   Stocks sold off to finish last week.
</P>
<P>
   But analysts say there appears to be some excitement attached to
Deutsche Telekom's purchase of VoiceStream Wireless.
</P>
<P>
   There's also a report that Nortel Networks is in talks with
Corning.
</P>
<P>
   At the same time, there is some earnings news out this morning.
Merck is among those posting better-than-expected numbers.
</P>
</TEXT>
