<HEADLINE> Three Killed in German Hotel Blast  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   BREMEN, Germany (AP) -- An explosion ripped through a hotel in a
town near Bremen early Monday, killing two men and a woman, police
said. They said they suspect the explosion was caused by a gas
leak.
</P>
<P>
   Police said three couples were staying in the hotel at the time
of the pre-dawn explosion in Thedinghausen, 10 miles southeast of
Bremen in northwest Germany.
</P>
<P>
   A German couple and a Swiss man were found dead in the rubble. A
Swiss woman was hospitalized with serious injuries, and another
German couple escaped the blast unhurt, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Police said late Monday that no one else was believed to have
been in the building and that search dogs had checked the area.
</P>
<P>
   Police spokesman Uwe Homes said the cause of the blast was still
undetermined, however, ''we suspect it was a gas explosion, but we
won't know for sure until the rubble is cleared away.''
</P>
<P>
   About three-quarters of the structure, which also houses a
restaurant and dance hall, was destroyed and the rest of the
building was in danger of collapsing, police said.
</P>
</TEXT>
