<BODY>
<HEADLINE> N.Y. Rangers Sign Two Goalies  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The New York Rangers agreed to terms Monday with
goalies Johan Holmqvist and Vitali Yeremeyev.
</P>
<P>
   Holmqvist, 22, played in 41 games with Brynas Gavle of the
Swedish Elite League last season. He had a 2.57 goals against
average and four shutouts. He was the Rangers' ninth selection,
175th overall, in the 1997 NHL Entry Draft.
</P>
<P>
   Yeremeyev, 24, appeared in 26 regular season games with Dynamo
Moscow of the Russian Hockey League, posting a league-leading 1.23
goals against average. Yeremeyev also tied for the league-lead with
seven shutouts.
</P>
<P>
   In 150 career games, Yeremeyev has a 1.82 GAA and 15 shutouts.
He was also in seven games at the 1998 Olympic Games in Nagano,
Japan with Team Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
   Yeremeyev was New York's 11th pick, 209th overall, in the 1994
NHL Entry Draft.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
