<HEADLINE> Cheney Quotes  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Selected comments on the selection of Dick Cheney as
running
mate for George W. Bush.
<TEXT>
<P>
   ''I think that Dick Cheney will really be an outstanding vice
president of the United States, and one that will garner
significant support throughout the party and the country.''
</P>
<P>
   --Arizona Sen. John McCain, who was in the running for the
running mate slot.
</P>
<P>
   ''I won't comment on candidates who are apparently under
consideration by Governor Bush.''
</P>
<P>
   --Vice President Al Gore, whose aides say he will comment after
Bush personally announces the choice. Gore is the likely Democratic
presidential nominee.
</P>
<P>
   ''Clearly people after coronary bypass surgery can be in superb
health with excellent quality of life, excellent productivity and
normal length of life. If he has a current physical examination,
which shows him in good health and his overall cardiac function is
good, I have absolutely no hesitation whatsoever''
</P>
<P>
   --Tennessee Sen. Bill Frist, a heart-lung surgeon on Cheney's
history of heart disease. Frist was on the list of possible running
mates.
</P>
<P>
   ''He makes a great vice presidential candidate. He will be
excellent in debates, a formidable debater, and an excellent
campaigner. He has been through any number of campaigns and he will
be a good counsel to candidate Bush.''
</P>
<P>
   --Tom Sansonetti, a longtime Cheney associate in Wyoming GOP
politics.
</P>
<P>
   ''He represents the quality, character and experience that
America is searching for in national leadership. He will help Gov.
Bush restore dignity to the political process and elevate the
debate of this campaign. And he would be a vice president America
can be proud of.''
</P>
<P>
   --Nebraska Sen. Chuck Hagel, who was also on the list of possible
running mates.
</P>
</TEXT>
