<HEADLINE> Henry Winkler Loses Emmy Bid  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Who would have thought a tough guy like the
Fonz could let an Emmy nomination get away?
</P>
<P>
   Henry Winkler, who played Fonzie on ''Happy Days,'' was ruled
ineligible for a comedy guest actor bid for ''Battery Park''
because the episode didn't air within the Emmy eligibility period.
</P>
<P>
   Winkler might yet be a winner: He's nominated in the drama guest
actor category for an appearance on ''The Practice.''
</P>
<P>
   ''The Lord giveth and the Lord taketh away,'' Winkler said. ''I
am thrilled to be nominated for 'The Practice' and 'Battery Park,'
even though it did not qualify.''
</P>
<P>
   His ''Battery Park'' episode was set to air in April, but the
low-rated sitcom was pulled by NBC. The half-hour featuring Winkler
didn't air until June, and the nomination cutoff date set by the
Academy of Television Arts &AMP; Sciences was May 31.
</P>
<P>
   William H. Macy will step into Winkler's spot with a nomination
for his work on ABC's ''Sports Night.'' He will compete with Bruce
Willis, Tom Selleck, Carl Reiner and Anthony LaPaglia. The
primetime Emmys are Sept. 10.
</P>
</TEXT>
