<HEADLINE> 20 Killed in Bolivia Truck Accident  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LA PAZ, Bolivia (AP) -- A truck carrying passengers careened over
a cliff in the Bolivian Andes Monday, killing 20 people and
injuring 10 others, police said.
</P>
<P>
   One passenger survived by jumping from the vehicle before it
tumbled 200 feet down a mountainside, said Police chief Col. Raul
Guardia.
</P>
<P>
   Police did not disclose what caused the crash, saying an
investigation was under way.
</P>
<P>
   Rescuers recovered the bodies late Monday and brought them back
to La Paz, 55 miles to the south.
</P>
<P>
   The twisting mountain road connecting La Paz to the tropical
region of Los Yungas has been labeled by the Bolivian media as
''the highway of death'' because of an especially high number of
accidents along it.
</P>
</TEXT>
