the Bolivian Andes Monday, killing 20 people and injuring 10 others, police
said. One passenger survived by jumping from the vehicle before it tumbled 200
feet down a mountainside, said Police chief Col. Raul Guardia. Police did not
disclose what caused the crash, saying an investigation was under way.
</P>
