game against Anaheim. Rodriguez, regarded by many as the best all-around catcher
in the majors, began the day batting .347 with 27 home runs and 83 RBIs.
Rodriguez was hurt when his thumb hit Mo Vaughn's bat on a swinging third strike
as he threw to second base on a steal attempt by Kevin Stocker.
