<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Virginia-based BWX Technologies ousts Mason &AMP; Hanger Corp. at Texas nuclear weapons plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   AMARILLO, Texas (AP) - The U.S. Department of Energy has awarded
BWX Technologies Inc. a five-year contract to run the Pantex
nuclear plant, ousting Mason &AMP; Hanger Corp., which has managed the
weapons assembly and disassembly operation for more than 40 years.
</P>
<P>
   A spokesman for Mason &AMP; Hanger's parent company told the
Amarillo Globe-News in a story for Tuesday's editions that Energy
Department officials informed company officials of the switch
Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The Energy Department was expected to make the announcement on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   ''Obviously, we were very disappointed that the Department of
Energy didn't select Day &AMP; Zimmermann. We're very proud of our work
and our achievements at Pantex,'' said David Fridling of Day &AMP;
Zimmermann Group Inc.
</P>
<P>
   Officials from Lynchburg, Va.-based BWX could not immediately be
reached for comment by The Associated Press Monday night.
</P>
<P>
   Mason &AMP; Hanger has held the Pantex contract since 1956, when it
took over weapons work from Procter &AMP; Gamble. The contract ends
Sept. 30.
</P>
<P>
   The Energy Department also turned down bids by Lockheed-Martin
and EG&AMP;G Inc.
</P>
<P>
   BWX Technologies supplies nuclear fuel and reactor components to
the U.S. Navy and has contracts for Energy Department operations at
the Idaho National Engineering and Environmental Laboratory and the
Oak Ridge National Laboratory.
</P>
<P>
   The company collaborated with Morris Township, N.J.-based
aerospace firm Honeywell Inc. and Frederick, M.D.-based Bechtel
National Inc., which has operations at more than 12 major Energy
Department facilities and labs in the United States.
</P>
<P>
   Pantex is the nation's primary nuclear weapons disassembly site
and serves as the interim storage site for more than 8,000 pits
from dismantled warheads.
</P>
<P>
   --:
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   BWX Technologies, Inc.: http://www.bwtx.com/bwxt.html
</P>
<P>
   U.S. Department of Energy: http://www.doe.gov
</P>
<P>
   Mason &AMP; Hanger: http://www.mhgrp.com
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
