<HEADLINE> Tractor trailer rollover in Buffalo  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   BUFFALO, N.Y. (AP) - A tractor trailer carrying 27,000 pounds of
grease rolled over in Buffalo Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Rescue crews say the truck driver couldn't maneuver a windy exit
ramp and ended up flipping the rig over, spilling pools of
Lithium-bearing grease on the road.
</P>
<P>
   The driver escaped the wreck unharmed and was found hunched over
the wall of the overpass.
</P>
<P>
   Emergency Medical Technician Rob Zimmerman was on his way to
work when he and another driver stopped to help the crash victim.
He said the truck was teetering on the bridge's edge when they
brought the victim to safety.
</P>
<P>
   Crews were able to right the truck.
</P>
<P>
   The roads were blocked while cleanup crews worked, causing hours
of delays.
</P>
</TEXT>
